### JIT Engine (Tree Shaking)

Tailwind v3's JIT engine generates CSS on-demand, scanning your templates and only producing the classes you actually use:

```js
// tailwind.config.js
module.exports = {
  content: [
    './src/**/*.{html,js,jsx,tsx}',
    './public/index.html',
  ],
}
```

### Content Paths Configuration

Proper content paths are crucial for JIT to find all classes:

```js
module.exports = {
  content: [
    // All template files
    './pages/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx}',
    './components/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx}',
    './layouts/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx}',

    // Include any file that uses Tailwind classes
    './safelist.txt',
  ],
}
```

### Safelisting Classes

Prevent specific classes from being purged:

```js
module.exports = {
  content: {
    files: ['./src/**/*.{html,js}'],
  },
  safelist: [
    'bg-red-500',
    'text-center',
    'lg:text-right',
    // Pattern matching
    {
      pattern: /bg-(red|green|blue)-(100|200|300)/,
    },
    // All variants
    {
      pattern: /text-(red|green|blue)-(400|500|600)/,
      variants: ['hover', 'focus'],
    },
  ],
}
```

### PurgeCSS in Tailwind v2

In Tailwind v2, purging was configured via `purge` instead of `content`:

```js
// Tailwind v2
module.exports = {
  purge: {
    content: ['./src/**/*.html'],
    options: {
      safelist: ['bg-red-500'],
    },
  },
}
```

### Production Build Optimization

```bash
# Build for production (minified + purged)
NODE_ENV=production npx tailwindcss -o build.css --minify

# Or use PostCSS CLI
NODE_ENV=production npx postcss src/styles.css -o public/styles.css
```

### File Size Best Practices

- **Use JIT engine** (Tailwind v3+) - automatically small output
- **Configure content paths precisely** - don't scan node_modules
- **Avoid dynamic class construction** - don't use template literals for class names

```html
<!-- Bad - JIT can't scan this -->
<div class="text-{{ size }}-{{ color }}">

<!-- Good - JIT sees full class names -->
<div class="{{ size === 'lg' ? 'text-lg' : 'text-base' }} {{ color === 'blue' ? 'text-blue-600' : 'text-gray-600' }}">
```

- **Use safelist sparingly** - only when absolutely necessary
- **Minify CSS output** with the `--minify` flag
- **Enable compression** (gzip/Brotli) on your web server
- **Use CSSNano** in your PostCSS workflow for additional minification

codeExample:
/* postcss.config.js - optimized for production */
module.exports = {
  plugins: {
    tailwindcss: {},
    autoprefixer: process.env.NODE_ENV === 'production' ? {} : false,
    cssnano: process.env.NODE_ENV === 'production' ? {} : false,
  },
}

/* tailwind.config.js - safelist example */
module.exports = {
  content: ['./src/**/*.{html,js}'],
  safelist: [
    'bg-green-500',
    'bg-red-500',
    'bg-yellow-500',
    { pattern: /^border-/ },
  ],
  theme: { extend: {} },
  plugins: [],
}

/* Build commands */
// Development: npx tailwindcss -i src/input.css -o dist/output.css --watch
// Production:  NODE_ENV=production npx tailwindcss -i src/input.css -o dist/output.css --minify
